Installation
------------

    $ git clone https://github.com/Daderus/dotvim.git ~/.vim

Create symlinks:

    $ ln -s ~/.vim/vimrc ~/.vimrc

Switch to the `~/.vim` directory, and fetch submodules:

    $ cd ~/.vim
    $ git submodule init
    $ git submodule update


Easy installation
-----------------

It is possible to start a script after git clone or pull to execute
needed installtion steps.
    
    $ cd ~/.vim
    $ ./install.sh


Plugin: Command-T
-----------------

Search file names quickly by typing parts of file name.

Prepare Command-t installation on Ubunty based systems:

    $sudo apt-get install ruby-dev

Build vim module:

    $ cd ~/.vim/ruby/command-t
    $ ruby extconf.rb
    $ make

Key mapping:

<leader>t       -> opens the commandt window


Plugin: Occur
-------------

Searchs text parts in current and in all open buffers. The found lines 
can be selected to jump to it.

Installation is done by git clone or pull

Key mapping:

<leader>ft      -> Find selected Text in current buffer
<leader>fb      -> Find selected text in all Buffers
<leader>fu      -> Find word Under cursor in all buffers


Plugin LustyExplorer
--------------------

LustyExplorer is a fast and responsive way to manage files and buffers 
in Vim.  It includes a filesystem explorer, a buffer switcher, and a 
buffer grep for searching through and switching between files and buffers 
quickly, all through a mostly common interface. 

Installation is done by copying the file 
https://raw.github.com/sjbach/lusty/master/plugin/lusty-explorer.vim
to ~/.vim/plugin

Key mapping:
<Leader>lf      -> Opens filesystem explorer.
<Leader>lr      -> Opens filesystem explorer at the directory of the current file.
<Leader>lb      -> Opens buffer explorer.
<Leader>lg      -> Opens buffer grep.


Plugin: ack.vim
----------------

This plugin is a front for the Perl module App::Ack. Ack can be used as 
a replacement for 99% of the uses of grep. This plugin will allow you to 
run ack from vim, and shows the results in a split window.

Installation
- Covered by script install.sh

Key mapping:
- not done yet



